## Core Principles

### 1. Transactional Development
**Every commit must result in a working application**

- ✅ All features must be complete and functional
- ✅ No half-implemented features in main branch
- ✅ Use feature flags for work-in-progress
- ❌ Never commit broken code
- ❌ Never commit features that crash the app

### 2. Scope Discipline
**Stay within current MVP phase unless explicitly told otherwise**

- ✅ Only implement features from current phase
- ✅ Document any scope expansion requests
- ❌ Don't add "nice to have" features
- ❌ Don't jump to future MVP phases

### 3. Zero-Cost Constraint
**All MVP1-3 features must work without paid services**

- ✅ Use mock data for AI suggestions
- ✅ Use free geocoding APIs (Nominatim)
- ✅ Use Vercel free tier
- ❌ Don't integrate paid AI services yet
- ❌ Don't use premium APIs

